        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 24 at 5:34PM EDT until July 24 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>SVRGRR

The National Weather Service in Grand Rapids has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Allegan County in southwestern Michigan...
Northwestern Kalamazoo County in southwestern Michigan...

* Until 630 PM EDT.

* At 533 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Bangor, or 11
miles east of South Haven, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Allegan...
Wayland...             Otsego...              Plainwell...
Parchment...           Martin...              Westwood...
Comstock Northwest...  Alamo...               Hopkins...
Bradley...             Pullman...             Oshtemo...
Green Lake...          Shelbyville...         Cooper...
Pine Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
